history.text: Did you get to read a document yet?
Yes I did
Ahh okay... not sure exactly what we are supposed to do. I did not read one.
I got one for 'John Wick', have you seen it?
I have not but it sounds interesting, whats it about?
It is about a hitman, who had left the life of killing behind, but after his wife died and his car got stolen by some Russian gangsters, he goes on the warpath
Oh wow. Are there any notable actors/actresses in this movie?
Keanu Reeves is the main character, which he really surprised me in this movie.
The Matrix dude?! Thats cool. What time period is this movie set in?
It seemed like right now
Modern, even better.... has this movie won any awards?
I do not believe so, films like this do not win awards usually
Hmm I see. What genre would you consider this movie?
Definitely action
Lots of shooting
Okay I actually want to watch this now!
I recommend it
The film has sort of a neo-noir quality to it

Thats always great as a fan of the Matrix trilogy. Do you happen to know if there is a sequel to this movie
 as well?
Yep, there is one, I believe it came out last year.
It was really solid, as well
Super cool, something that can captivate for longer than one movie is fantastic.
It certainly does that
I'm not sure what else we are supposed to do.... I am just waiting to be able to go look up this movie lol
I do not want to spoil the details of it for you
What rating does this movie have? Such as, PG 13, R, etc?
I would think R, but it does not say on the document, at least where I can find it...
Thanks so much for explaining all these details to me. I certainly feel like I know a lot about this movie now and know if I should spend my time viewing it.
As I said earlier, I highly recommend it, and the sequel
(how do we finish this task?)

uid1response.feedback: I wasnt given a document to read but I did have to get recommendations from someone else. They were able to explain to me the main storyline of the movie along with the main actor, possible movie rating of R even though it wasnt listed, it was super helpful to know that. Also knowing there is a sequel is awesome cause I hate movies that end on cliffhangers that never pick back up!
